OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F145A1698919488
OL,3,CUK transmitter network hit by
OL,4,Celectricity bill increase
OL,6,FThe nature of digital TV and radio
OL,7,Fmeans there's at least several
OL,8,Fchannels running a comprehensive
OL,9,Fschedule through the night on most
OL,10,Fmultiplexes.
OL,12,FHowever, it's interesting to note
OL,13,Fthat many mobile networks ` some of
OL,14,Fwhich operate via the same masts as
OL,15,Fdigital TV services ` are turning off
OL,16,Fsites, reducing power and/or
OL,17,Fbandwidth during the night, as they
OL,18,Fgrapple with rising costs.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,Uppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
FL,146,144,8ff,8ff,8ff,8ff
PN,14503
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F145A1698919488
OL,3,CUK transmitter network hit by
OL,4,Celectricity bill increase
OL,6,FAs a result, it's possible that your
OL,7,Fmobile signal switches to a different
OL,8,Fmast after midnight, or the available
OL,9,Fbandwidth is reduced ` a move that
OL,10,Fwon't affect most users as there's
OL,11,Fless demand overnight, when users
OL,12,Ftend to be at home and connected to a
OL,13,Flocal Wi-Fi connection, or even
OL,14,Fasleep and not using data!
OL,16,FSome mobile connections are more
OL,17,Fenergy intensive than others. That's
OL,18,Fone of the reasons why 3G is being
OL,19,Fretired. Vodafone says just sending a
OL,20,Fterabyte of data via 5G uses 7% of
OL,21,Fthe energy used to send the same
OL,22,Famount of data on 3G.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,Uppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
FL,146,144,8ff,8ff,8ff,8ff
PN,14504
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F145A1698919488
OL,3,CUK transmitter network hit by
OL,4,Celectricity bill increase
OL,6,FWhile it might be tempting to think
OL,7,Fthat closing TV masts down, perhaps
OL,8,Frelay sites, would be a good way of
OL,9,Fsaving energy, these masts could form
OL,10,Fthe bedrock of a future 5G Broadcast
OL,11,Fnetwork. That's something engineers
OL,12,Fin a number of countries are looking
OL,13,Fat, with trials already underway in
OL,14,Fplaces.
OL,16,FThe current network of main and relay
OL,17,Ftransmitter sites could create a mesh
OL,18,Fnetwork covering most of the UK, so
OL,19,Fit wouldn't be an ideal time now to
OL,20,Fcut the number of relay sites, as it
OL,21,Fmay be difficult to gain planning
OL,22,Fpermission again.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
